T15:33:12.000Z","msg":"Central vision is relatively weak in the dark (scotopic vision) since cone cells lack sensitivity at low light levels. Rod cells, which are concentrated further away from the fovea, operate better than cone cells in low light. This makes peripheral vision useful for detecting faint light sources at night (like faint stars)."},{"pid":"050f3a35a682c13e60ad26203fe3dab8e1684d58","tid":852125,"uid":210297,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-07T15:35:01.000Z","msg":"邊緣既視網膜多啲rod cells 佢地對低光敏感但只有黑白影像， 而中央嘅視網膜多cone cells, 佢地對低光唔敏感但睇到顏色"},{"pid":"4937ee2f22466f47ab8a1346c5233ecbb7502be6","tid":852125,"uid":34023,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-07T15:38:31.000Z","msg":"IG effect"}]}